Class MethodTest

java.lang.Object
MethodTest
Direct Known Subclasses:
MethodTestFailure
public class MethodTest
extends java.lang.Object
A specialized way to build a specific test case for a Method. Methods are then compared for equality by invocation of the assertEquality method.

    • assertEquality

      public TestingTuple assertEquality​(MethodTest methodTest)
      A method to check if two methods are equal. Invoke this from the expected object, and pass the generated MethodTest to this method to compare it for equality.
      Parameters:
      methodTest - the MethodTest to compare equality. Generally, this is the actual method to compare against
      Returns:
      true if equal, false if not.

    • observeModifier

      private void observeModifier​(java.lang.String modifierName)
      Updates the modifier array with the given state for its given name. Modifiers are organized in the array in the following fashion.

      [0] -> public [1] -> private [2] -> protected [3] -> static [4] -> final [5] -> transient [6] -> abstract [7] -> native [8] -> interface [9] -> strict [10] -> synchronized [11] -> volatile

      Parameters:
      modifierName - The modifier name to set, in all lowercase.
